                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5 &#177; .5 v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>CMP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5 &#177; .5 v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>MAP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5 &#177; .5 v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" morerows="2">
                            <para>If disconnecting a sensor causes V Ref to be present at a circuit that had previously
                                lost V Ref it is likely that the disconnected sensor had shorted V Ref to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>APS/IVS</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
