                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">(Check with Sensor Connector(s). Disconnected and ignitionkey OFF, all
                                    accessories off)
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Sensor</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>ICP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>B to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>> 1000 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" morerows="2">
                            <para>Resistance &#60; 1000 ohms indicates a short to grd. If a short to grd condition is
                                identified, remove all sensor connectors that are connected to V Ref and ECM to
                                determine if short is in a sensor. ECM or wire harness.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
